{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XXPBffpmhyMcyU27bKTo41","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t<workflow>\n2\t  <critical>The workflow execution engine is governed by: {project-root}/_bmad/core/tasks/workflow.xml</critical>\n3\t  <critical>You MUST have already loaded and processed: {installed_path}/workflow.yaml</critical>\n4\t  <critical>Communicate all responses in {communication_language} and generate all documents in {document_output_language}</critical>\n5\t\n6\t  <critical>🔥 CRITICAL MISSION: You are creating the ULTIMATE story context engine that prevents LLM developer mistakes, omissions or\n7\t    disasters! 🔥</critical>\n8\t  <critical>Your purpose is NOT to copy from epics - it's to create a comprehensive, optimized story file that gives the DEV agent\n9\t    EVERYTHING needed for flawless implementation</critical>\n10\t  <critical>COMMON LLM MISTAKES TO PREVENT: reinventing wheels, wrong libraries, wrong file locations, breaking regressions, ignoring UX,\n11\t    vague implementations, lying about completion, not learning from past work</critical>\n12\t  <critical>🚨 EXHAUSTIVE ANALYSIS REQUIRED: You must thoroughly analyze ALL artifacts to extract critical context - do NOT be lazy or skim!\n13\t    This is the most important function in the entire development process!</critical>\n14\t  <critical>🔬 UTILIZE SUBPROCESSES AND SUBAGENTS: Use research subagents, subprocesses or parallel processing if available to thoroughly\n15\t    analyze different artifacts simultaneously and thoroughly</critical>\n16\t  <critical>❓ SAVE QUESTIONS: If you think of questions or clarifications during analysis, save them for the end after the complete story is\n17\t    written</critical>\n18\t  <critical>🎯 ZERO USER INTERVENTION: Process should be fully automated except for initial epic/story selection or missing documents</critical>\n19\t\n20\t  <step n=\"1\" goal=\"Determine target story\">\n21\t    <check if=\"{{story_path}} is provided by user or user provided the epic and story number such as 2-4 or 1.6 or epic 1 story 5\">\n22\t      <action>Parse user-provided story path: extract epic_num, story_num, story_title from format like \"1-2-user-auth\"</action>\n23\t      <action>Set {{epic_num}}, {{story_num}}, {{story_key}} from user input</action>\n24\t      <action>GOTO step 2a</action>\n25\t    </check>\n26\t\n27\t    <action>Check if {{sprint_status}} file exists for auto discover</action>\n28\t    <check if=\"sprint status file does NOT exist\">\n29\t      <output>🚫 No sprint status file found and no story specified</output>\n30\t      <output>\n31\t        **Required Options:**\n32\t        1. Run `sprint-planning` to initialize sprint tracking (recommended)\n33\t        2. Provide specific epic-story number to create (e.g., \"1-2-user-auth\")\n34\t        3. Provide path to story documents if sprint status doesn't exist yet\n35\t      </output>\n36\t      <ask>Choose option [1], provide epic-story number, path to story docs, or [q] to quit:</ask>\n37\t\n38\t      <check if=\"user chooses 'q'\">\n39\t        <action>HALT - No work needed</action>\n40\t      </check>\n41\t\n42\t      <check if=\"user chooses '1'\">\n43\t        <output>Run sprint-planning workflow first to create sprint-status.yaml</output>\n44\t        <action>HALT - User needs to run sprint-planning</action>\n45\t      </check>\n46\t\n47\t      <check if=\"user provides epic-story number\">\n48\t        <action>Parse user input: extract epic_num, story_num, story_title</action>\n49\t        <action>Set {{epic_num}}, {{story_num}}, {{story_key}} from user input</action>\n50\t        <action>GOTO step 2a</action>\n51\t      </check>\n52\t\n53\t      <check if=\"user provides story docs path\">\n54\t        <action>Use user-provided path for story documents</action>\n55\t        <action>GOTO step 2a</action>\n56\t      </check>\n57\t    </check>\n58\t\n59\t    <!-- Auto-discover from sprint status only if no user input -->\n60\t    <check if=\"no user input provided\">\n61\t      <critical>MUST read COMPLETE {sprint_status} file from start to end to preserve order</critical>\n62\t      <action>Load the FULL file: {{sprint_status}}</action>\n63\t      <action>Read ALL lines from beginning to end - do not skip any content</action>\n64\t      <action>Parse the development_status section completely</action>\n65\t\n66\t      <action>Find the FIRST story (by reading in order from top to bottom) where:\n67\t        - Key matches pattern: number-number-name (e.g., \"1-2-user-auth\")\n68\t        - NOT an epic key (epic-X) or retrospective (epic-X-retrospective)\n69\t        - Status value equals \"backlog\"\n70\t      </action>\n71\t\n72\t      <check if=\"no backlog story found\">\n73\t        <output>📋 No backlog stories found in sprint-status.yaml\n74\t\n75\t          All stories are either already created, in progress, or done.\n76\t\n77\t          **Options:**\n78\t          1. Run sprint-planning to refresh story tracking\n79\t          2. Load PM agent and run correct-course to add more stories\n80\t          3. Check if current sprint is complete and run retrospective\n81\t        </output>\n82\t        <action>HALT</action>\n83\t      </check>\n84\t\n85\t      <action>Extract from found story key (e.g., \"1-2-user-authentication\"):\n86\t        - epic_num: first number before dash (e.g., \"1\")\n87\t        - story_num: second number after first dash (e.g., \"2\")\n88\t        - story_title: remainder after second dash (e.g., \"user-authentication\")\n89\t      </action>\n90\t      <action>Set {{story_id}} = \"{{epic_num}}.{{story_num}}\"</action>\n91\t      <action>Store story_key for later use (e.g., \"1-2-user-authentication\")</action>\n92\t\n93\t      <!-- Mark epic as in-progress if this is first story -->\n94\t      <action>Check if this is the first story in epic {{epic_num}} by looking for {{epic_num}}-1-* pattern</action>\n95\t      <check if=\"this is first story in epic {{epic_num}}\">\n96\t        <action>Load {{sprint_status}} and check epic-{{epic_num}} status</action>\n97\t        <action>If epic status is \"backlog\" → update to \"in-progress\"</action>\n98\t        <action>If epic status is \"contexted\" (legacy status) → update to \"in-progress\" (backward compatibility)</action>\n99\t        <action>If epic status is \"in-progress\" → no change needed</action>\n100\t        <check if=\"epic status is 'done'\">\n101\t          <output>🚫 ERROR: Cannot create story in completed epic</output>\n102\t          <output>Epic {{epic_num}} is marked as 'done'. All stories are complete.</output>\n103\t          <output>If you need to add more work, either:</output>\n104\t          <output>1. Manually change epic status back to 'in-progress' in sprint-status.yaml</output>\n105\t          <output>2. Create a new epic for additional work</output>\n106\t          <action>HALT - Cannot proceed</action>\n107\t        </check>\n108\t        <check if=\"epic status is not one of: backlog, contexted, in-progress, done\">\n109\t          <output>🚫 ERROR: Invalid epic status '{{epic_status}}'</output>\n110\t          <output>Epic {{epic_num}} has invalid status. Expected: backlog, in-progress, or done</output>\n111\t          <output>Please fix sprint-status.yaml manually or run sprint-planning to regenerate</output>\n112\t          <action>HALT - Cannot proceed</action>\n113\t        </check>\n114\t        <output>📊 Epic {{epic_num}} status updated to in-progress</output>\n115\t      </check>\n116\t\n117\t      <action>GOTO step 2a</action>\n118\t    </check>\n119\t    <action>Load the FULL file: {{sprint_status}}</action>\n120\t    <action>Read ALL lines from beginning to end - do not skip any content</action>\n121\t    <action>Parse the development_status section completely</action>\n122\t\n123\t    <action>Find the FIRST story (by reading in order from top to bottom) where:\n124\t      - Key matches pattern: number-number-name (e.g., \"1-2-user-auth\")\n125\t      - NOT an epic key (epic-X) or retrospective (epic-X-retrospective)\n126\t      - Status value equals \"backlog\"\n127\t    </action>\n128\t\n129\t    <check if=\"no backlog story found\">\n130\t      <output>📋 No backlog stories found in sprint-status.yaml\n131\t\n132\t        All stories are either already created, in progress, or done.\n133\t\n134\t        **Options:**\n135\t        1. Run sprint-planning to refresh story tracking\n136\t        2. Load PM agent and run correct-course to add more stories\n137\t        3. Check if current sprint is complete and run retrospective\n138\t      </output>\n139\t      <action>HALT</action>\n140\t    </check>\n141\t\n142\t    <action>Extract from found story key (e.g., \"1-2-user-authentication\"):\n143\t      - epic_num: first number before dash (e.g., \"1\")\n144\t      - story_num: second number after first dash (e.g., \"2\")\n145\t      - story_title: remainder after second dash (e.g., \"user-authentication\")\n146\t    </action>\n147\t    <action>Set {{story_id}} = \"{{epic_num}}.{{story_num}}\"</action>\n148\t    <action>Store story_key for later use (e.g., \"1-2-user-authentication\")</action>\n149\t\n150\t    <!-- Mark epic as in-progress if this is first story -->\n151\t    <action>Check if this is the first story in epic {{epic_num}} by looking for {{epic_num}}-1-* pattern</action>\n152\t    <check if=\"this is first story in epic {{epic_num}}\">\n153\t      <action>Load {{sprint_status}} and check epic-{{epic_num}} status</action>\n154\t      <action>If epic status is \"backlog\" → update to \"in-progress\"</action>\n155\t      <action>If epic status is \"contexted\" (legacy status) → update to \"in-progress\" (backward compatibility)</action>\n156\t      <action>If epic status is \"in-progress\" → no change needed</action>\n157\t      <check if=\"epic status is 'done'\">\n158\t        <output>🚫 ERROR: Cannot create story in completed epic</output>\n159\t        <output>Epic {{epic_num}} is marked as 'done'. All stories are complete.</output>\n160\t        <output>If you need to add more work, either:</output>\n161\t        <output>1. Manually change epic status back to 'in-progress' in sprint-status.yaml</output>\n162\t        <output>2. Create a new epic for additional work</output>\n163\t        <action>HALT - Cannot proceed</action>\n164\t      </check>\n165\t      <check if=\"epic status is not one of: backlog, contexted, in-progress, done\">\n166\t        <output>🚫 ERROR: Invalid epic status '{{epic_status}}'</output>\n167\t        <output>Epic {{epic_num}} has invalid status. Expected: backlog, in-progress, or done</output>\n168\t        <output>Please fix sprint-status.yaml manually or run sprint-planning to regenerate</output>\n169\t        <action>HALT - Cannot proceed</action>\n170\t      </check>\n171\t      <output>📊 Epic {{epic_num}} status updated to in-progress</output>\n172\t    </check>\n173\t\n174\t    <action>GOTO step 2a</action>\n175\t  </step>\n176\t\n177\t  <step n=\"2\" goal=\"Load and analyze core artifacts\">\n178\t    <critical>🔬 EXHAUSTIVE ARTIFACT ANALYSIS - This is where you prevent future developer fuckups!</critical>\n179\t\n180\t    <!-- Load all available content through discovery protocol -->\n181\t    <invoke-protocol\n182\t      name=\"discover_inputs\" />\n183\t    <note>Available content: {epics_content}, {prd_content}, {architecture_content}, {ux_content},\n184\t    {project_context}</note>\n185\t\n186\t    <!-- Analyze epics file for story foundation -->\n187\t    <action>From {epics_content}, extract Epic {{epic_num}} complete context:</action> **EPIC ANALYSIS:** - Epic\n188\t    objectives and business value - ALL stories in this epic for cross-story context - Our specific story's requirements, user story\n189\t    statement, acceptance criteria - Technical requirements and constraints - Dependencies on other stories/epics - Source hints pointing to\n190\t    original documents <!-- Extract specific story requirements -->\n191\t    <action>Extract our story ({{epic_num}}-{{story_num}}) details:</action> **STORY FOUNDATION:** - User story statement\n192\t    (As a, I want, so that) - Detailed acceptance criteria (already BDD formatted) - Technical requirements specific to this story -\n193\t    Business context and value - Success criteria\n194\t\n195\t    <!-- SPEC COVERAGE PASS: ACs from epics are a starting point, not the final set -->\n196\t    <critical>🎯 SPEC COVERAGE — ACs must cover UX/PRD behavioral requirements, not just epic bullet points!</critical>\n197\t    <action>Cross-reference epic ACs against {ux_content} and {prd_content} for this story's scope:\n198\t      - For each UX/PRD behavioral requirement within this story's scope, check if an existing AC covers it\n199\t      - If a requirement has no matching AC, draft a new AC that describes the observable user-facing behavior\n200\t      - ACs must describe WHAT THE USER SEES OR EXPERIENCES, not implementation artifacts\n201\t        BAD:  \"Given startRenderer() is called, Then it returns a RendererHandle with update() method\"\n202\t        GOOD: \"Given Claude is executing tools, When the operator watches the terminal, Then they see each active tool with a spinner and completed tools as permanent lines\"\n203\t      - Each AC should be verifiable by observing the running system, not just by reading code\n204\t      - Balance: cover all spec requirements but don't over-specify implementation details\n205\t    </action>\n206\t    <action>Store the merged AC list (epic ACs + spec-derived ACs) as the final acceptance criteria for the story</action>\n207\t\n208\t    <!-- Previous story analysis for context continuity -->\n209\t    <check if=\"story_num > 1\">\n210\t      <action>Find {{previous_story_num}}: scan {implementation_artifacts} for the story file in epic {{epic_num}} with the highest story number less than {{story_num}}</action>\n211\t      <action>Load previous story file: {implementation_artifacts}/{{epic_num}}-{{previous_story_num}}-*.md</action> **PREVIOUS STORY INTELLIGENCE:** -\n212\t    Dev notes and learnings from previous story - Review feedback and corrections needed - Files that were created/modified and their\n213\t    patterns - Testing approaches that worked/didn't work - Problems encountered and solutions found - Code patterns established <action>Extract\n214\t    all learnings that could impact current story implementation</action>\n215\t    </check>\n216\t\n217\t    <!-- Git intelligence for previous work patterns -->\n218\t    <check\n219\t      if=\"previous story exists AND git repository detected\">\n220\t      <action>Get last 5 commit titles to understand recent work patterns</action>\n221\t      <action>Analyze 1-5 most recent commits for relevance to current story:\n222\t        - Files created/modified\n223\t        - Code patterns and conventions used\n224\t        - Library dependencies added/changed\n225\t        - Architecture decisions implemented\n226\t        - Testing approaches used\n227\t      </action>\n228\t      <action>Extract actionable insights for current story implementation</action>\n229\t    </check>\n230\t  </step>\n231\t\n232\t  <step n=\"3\" goal=\"Architecture analysis for developer guardrails\">\n233\t    <critical>🏗️ ARCHITECTURE INTELLIGENCE - Extract everything the developer MUST follow!</critical> **ARCHITECTURE DOCUMENT ANALYSIS:** <action>Systematically\n234\t    analyze architecture content for story-relevant requirements:</action>\n235\t\n236\t    <!-- Load architecture - single file or sharded -->\n237\t    <check if=\"architecture file is single file\">\n238\t      <action>Load complete {architecture_content}</action>\n239\t    </check>\n240\t    <check if=\"architecture is sharded to folder\">\n241\t      <action>Load architecture index and scan all architecture files</action>\n242\t    </check> **CRITICAL ARCHITECTURE EXTRACTION:** <action>For\n243\t    each architecture section, determine if relevant to this story:</action> - **Technical Stack:** Languages, frameworks, libraries with\n244\t    versions - **Code Structure:** Folder organization, naming conventions, file patterns - **API Patterns:** Service structure, endpoint\n245\t    patterns, data contracts - **Database Schemas:** Tables, relationships, constraints relevant to story - **Security Requirements:**\n246\t    Authentication patterns, authorization rules - **Performance Requirements:** Caching strategies, optimization patterns - **Testing\n247\t    Standards:** Testing frameworks, coverage expectations, test patterns - **Deployment Patterns:** Environment configurations, build\n248\t    processes - **Integration Patterns:** External service integrations, data flows <action>Extract any story-specific requirements that the\n249\t    developer MUST follow</action>\n250\t    <action>Identify any architectural decisions that override previous patterns</action>\n251\t  </step>\n252\t\n253\t  <step n=\"4\" goal=\"Web research for latest technical specifics\">\n254\t    <critical>🌐 ENSURE LATEST TECH KNOWLEDGE - Prevent outdated implementations!</critical> **WEB INTELLIGENCE:** <action>Identify specific\n255\t    technical areas that require latest version knowledge:</action>\n256\t\n257\t    <!-- Check for libraries/frameworks mentioned in architecture -->\n258\t    <action>From architecture analysis, identify specific libraries, APIs, or\n259\t    frameworks</action>\n260\t    <action>For each critical technology, research latest stable version and key changes:\n261\t      - Latest API documentation and breaking changes\n262\t      - Security vulnerabilities or updates\n263\t      - Performance improvements or deprecations\n264\t      - Best practices for current version\n265\t    </action>\n266\t    **EXTERNAL CONTEXT INCLUSION:** <action>Include in story any critical latest information the developer needs:\n267\t      - Specific library versions and why chosen\n268\t      - API endpoints with parameters and authentication\n269\t      - Recent security patches or considerations\n270\t      - Performance optimization techniques\n271\t      - Migration considerations if upgrading\n272\t    </action>\n273\t  </step>\n274\t\n275\t  <step n=\"5\" goal=\"Create comprehensive story file\">\n276\t    <critical>📝 CREATE ULTIMATE STORY FILE - The developer's master implementation guide!</critical>\n277\t\n278\t    <action>Initialize from template.md:\n279\t    {default_output_file}</action>\n280\t    <template-output file=\"{default_output_file}\">story_header</template-output>\n281\t\n282\t    <!-- Story foundation from epics analysis -->\n283\t    <template-output\n284\t      file=\"{default_output_file}\">story_requirements</template-output>\n285\t\n286\t    <!-- FINAL AC QUALITY CHECK before writing the rest of the story -->\n287\t    <critical>🔍 AC QUALITY GATE — Review ACs before finalizing the story file</critical>\n288\t    <action>Before proceeding, review every AC in the story file:\n289\t      1. Does each AC describe observable user-facing behavior (not just code artifacts)?\n290\t         - REJECT: \"function X exists\", \"module exports Y\", \"returns RendererHandle\"\n291\t         - ACCEPT: \"operator sees X in the terminal\", \"command outputs Y\", \"dashboard displays Z\"\n292\t      2. Is every behavioral requirement from the UX spec and PRD (within this story's scope) covered by at least one AC?\n293\t         - If not, add the missing AC now\n294\t      3. Are ACs balanced — specific enough to verify but not so narrow they miss the spirit of the requirement?\n295\t         - A single AC like \"header shows story key\" is too narrow if the spec says \"header shows story key, phase, elapsed time, and progress\"\n296\t         - Combine related display elements into one AC that covers the full expected output\n297\t      4. Can each AC be verified by running the system and observing output (not just reading source code)?\n298\t    </action>\n299\t\n300\t    <!-- VERIFICATION TIER TAGGING — every AC must get a tier tag -->\n301\t    <critical>🏷️ VERIFICATION TIER TAGGING — Append a tier tag to every AC</critical>\n302\t    <action>For each AC in the story file, append a verification tier tag using the format:\n303\t      `&lt;!-- verification: {tier} --&gt;`\n304\t      where {tier} is one of: `test-provable`, `runtime-provable`, `environment-provable`, `escalate`.\n305\t\n306\t      **Tier Decision Tree — assign the LOWEST tier that can verify the AC:**\n307\t\n308\t      - `test-provable` — AC can be verified by building the project and running tests, linters, type checks, or grep.\n309\t        No running application needed. Criteria: code structure, types, file existence, test passing,\n310\t        documentation changes, config changes, refactoring, module exports, file line counts.\n311\t      - `runtime-provable` — AC requires running the built application and checking its behavior.\n312\t        No Docker stack needed. Criteria: CLI output, API endpoint behavior, exit codes, HTTP responses,\n313\t        process lifecycle, server startup, command-line flags.\n314\t      - `environment-provable` — AC requires a full environment (Docker stack, database, observability, multi-service).\n315\t        Criteria: Docker containers, databases, observability stack (logs/metrics/traces), multiple services\n316\t        communicating, distributed system behavior.\n317\t      - `escalate` — AC genuinely cannot be automated. This is rare.\n318\t        Criteria: physical hardware, human visual judgment, paid external services, GPU-dependent rendering.\n319\t\n320\t      **Concrete Examples (one per tier):**\n321\t\n322\t      - `test-provable`: Given the VerificationTier type in types.ts, when inspected, then it includes all four tier names\n323\t        `&lt;!-- verification: test-provable --&gt;`\n324\t      - `runtime-provable`: Given the CLI is invoked with `--help`, when the process runs, then it prints usage information and exits 0\n325\t        `&lt;!-- verification: runtime-provable --&gt;`\n326\t      - `environment-provable`: Given a request is sent to the API, when the observability stack is running, then the request appears in VictoriaLogs\n327\t        `&lt;!-- verification: environment-provable --&gt;`\n328\t      - `escalate`: Given the dashboard is rendered on a mobile device, when a human reviews it, then the layout is visually correct\n329\t        `&lt;!-- verification: escalate --&gt;`\n330\t\n331\t      **Default to `test-provable` when unsure.**\n332\t\n333\t      Do NOT use legacy tier names (`cli-verifiable`, `integration-required`, `unit-testable`, `black-box`).\n334\t      Only the four tiers above are valid for new stories.\n335\t    </action>\n336\t\n337\t    <!-- Developer context section - MOST IMPORTANT PART -->\n338\t    <template-output file=\"{default_output_file}\">\n339\t    developer_context_section</template-output> **DEV AGENT GUARDRAILS:** <template-output file=\"{default_output_file}\">\n340\t    technical_requirements</template-output>\n341\t    <template-output file=\"{default_output_file}\">architecture_compliance</template-output>\n342\t    <template-output\n343\t      file=\"{default_output_file}\">library_framework_requirements</template-output>\n344\t    <template-output file=\"{default_output_file}\">\n345\t    file_structure_requirements</template-output>\n346\t    <template-output file=\"{default_output_file}\">testing_requirements</template-output>\n347\t\n348\t    <!-- Previous story intelligence -->\n349\t    <check\n350\t      if=\"previous story learnings available\">\n351\t      <template-output file=\"{default_output_file}\">previous_story_intelligence</template-output>\n352\t    </check>\n353\t\n354\t    <!-- Git intelligence -->\n355\t    <check\n356\t      if=\"git analysis completed\">\n357\t      <template-output file=\"{default_output_file}\">git_intelligence_summary</template-output>\n358\t    </check>\n359\t\n360\t    <!-- Latest technical specifics -->\n361\t    <check if=\"web research completed\">\n362\t      <template-output file=\"{default_output_file}\">latest_tech_information</template-output>\n363\t    </check>\n364\t\n365\t    <!-- Project context reference -->\n366\t    <template-output\n367\t      file=\"{default_output_file}\">project_context_reference</template-output>\n368\t\n369\t    <!-- Final status update -->\n370\t    <template-output file=\"{default_output_file}\">\n371\t    story_completion_status</template-output>\n372\t\n373\t    <!-- CRITICAL: Set status to ready-for-dev -->\n374\t    <action>Set story Status to: \"ready-for-dev\"</action>\n375\t    <action>Add completion note: \"Ultimate\n376\t    context engine analysis completed - comprehensive developer guide created\"</action>\n377\t  </step>\n378\t\n379\t  <step n=\"6\" goal=\"Update sprint status and finalize\">\n380\t    <invoke-task>Validate against checklist at {installed_path}/checklist.md using _bmad/core/tasks/validate-workflow.xml</invoke-task>\n381\t    <action>Save story document unconditionally</action>\n382\t\n383\t    <!-- Update sprint status -->\n384\t    <check if=\"sprint status file exists\">\n385\t      <action>Update {{sprint_status}}</action>\n386\t      <action>Load the FULL file and read all development_status entries</action>\n387\t      <action>Find development_status key matching {{story_key}}</action>\n388\t      <action>Verify current status is \"backlog\" (expected previous state)</action>\n389\t      <action>Update development_status[{{story_key}}] = \"ready-for-dev\"</action>\n390\t      <action>Save file, preserving ALL comments and structure including STATUS DEFINITIONS</action>\n391\t    </check>\n392\t\n393\t    <action>Report completion</action>\n394\t    <output>**🎯 ULTIMATE BMad Method STORY CONTEXT CREATED, {user_name}!**\n395\t\n396\t      **Story Details:**\n397\t      - Story ID: {{story_id}}\n398\t      - Story Key: {{story_key}}\n399\t      - File: {{story_file}}\n400\t      - Status: ready-for-dev\n401\t\n402\t      **Next Steps:**\n403\t      1. Review the comprehensive story in {{story_file}}\n404\t      2. Run dev agents `dev-story` for optimized implementation\n405\t      3. Run `code-review` when complete (auto-marks done)\n406\t      4. Optional: If Test Architect module installed, run `/bmad:tea:automate` after `dev-story` to generate guardrail tests\n407\t\n408\t      **The developer now has everything needed for flawless implementation!**\n409\t    </output>\n410\t  </step>\n411\t\n412\t</workflow>\n413\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0163BvoEdufpS4RkXNcR2GmH","session_id":"90f775a4-0bf0-4884-b410-4d7f1f50684d","uuid":"c7bebaa6-46d3-4cd4-9f34-5d03373ac8a5","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:08:26.885Z"}
