{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HEkYuxKn9zsXE7BKCAVMMZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0195NzNnwDR3e3TVJMrjGgby","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-5-workflow-engine-driver-integration.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1070,"cache_read_input_tokens":32139,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1070,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":61,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0163BvoEdufpS4RkXNcR2GmH","session_id":"90f775a4-0bf0-4884-b410-4d7f1f50684d","uuid":"fcdc93f6-7c2b-4ea2-903b-8fb0cb765789"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016casA5PcJ13MqFxbPmB69V","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tstepsCompleted: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8]\n3\tlastStep: 8\n4\tstatus: 'complete'\n5\tcompletedAt: '2026-04-03'\n6\tinputDocuments:\n7\t  - prd.md (multi-framework orchestration PRD, 2026-04-03)\n8\t  - architecture.md (existing v1 architecture, brownfield context)\n9\t  - prd-validation-report.md (validation report, 4.5/5 Pass)\n10\tworkflowType: 'architecture'\n11\tproject_name: 'codeharness'\n12\tuser_name: 'BMad'\n13\tdate: '2026-04-03'\n14\t---\n15\t\n16\t# Architecture Decision Document\n17\t\n18\t_This document builds collaboratively through step-by-step discovery. Sections are appended as we work through each architectural decision together._\n19\t\n20\t## Project Context Analysis\n21\t\n22\t### Requirements Overview\n23\t\n24\t**Functional Requirements:**\n25\t38 FRs across 9 capability areas. The core is a driver abstraction layer (FR1-FR10) that normalizes 3 agent framework CLIs into a common `AgentDriver` interface with `StreamEvent` output. The workflow engine gains per-task `driver` and `model` fields (FR11-FR15). Cross-framework task execution uses explicit output contracts serialized as JSON (FR16-FR20). The Ink TUI gains a workflow graph component (FR24-FR30). Plugin ecosystem integration (gstack/omo) passes config to parent driver CLIs (FR21-FR23).\n26\t\n27\t**Non-Functional Requirements:**\n28\t18 NFRs across performance (driver spawn <3s, TUI update <500ms, health check <5s), integration (pinned CLI versions, backward-compatible schema, no plugin modifications), and reliability (crash detection <5s, atomic contract writes, idempotent re-runs). Single-user local CLI — no scalability or availability requirements.\n29\t\n30\t**Scale & Complexity:**\n31\t\n32\t- Primary domain: Node.js CLI extending existing Commander.js architecture\n33\t- Complexity level: Medium — one new architectural layer (drivers) on proven foundation\n34\t- Estimated architectural components: ~8 new (3 drivers, 1 driver factory, 1 output contract module, 1 TUI workflow component, workflow schema extension, model resolver)\n35\t\n36\t### Technical Constraints & Dependencies\n37\t\n38\t- **Existing architecture** — 10 decisions from v1 architecture remain valid: CLI↔Plugin boundary, state management, beads integration, template embedding, verification pipeline. This PRD extends, not replaces.\n39\t- **Agent SDK** — Claude Code Agent SDK (`@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`) already in use for in-process dispatch. Stays as the claude-code driver implementation.\n40\t- **Codex CLI** — External binary (`codex`). Output format must be reverse-engineered from real CLI output. Auth via OpenAI API key or ChatGPT account.\n41\t- **OpenCode CLI** — External binary (`opencode`). Go-based. Output format must be reverse-engineered. Supports 75+ models with per-provider keys.\n42\t- **No programmatic SDK** — Neither Codex nor OpenCode expose a dispatch SDK. All integration is CLI wrapping via `child_process.spawn` with stdout/stderr parsing.\n43\t- **Ink/React TUI** — Existing TUI uses Ink 6 with React 19. New workflow graph component must fit the existing component architecture and 15 FPS render loop.\n44\t- **Workflow YAML schema** — Existing `workflow.schema.json` must be extended (not replaced) with `driver` and `model` fields. JSON Schema backward compatibility required.\n45\t\n46\t### Cross-Cutting Concerns Identified\n47\t\n48\t1. **Driver lifecycle management** — Spawning, monitoring, timeout, termination, crash recovery applies to all drivers. Must be uniform regardless of whether the driver is in-process (Agent SDK) or CLI-wrapped (Codex, OpenCode).\n49\t2. **Stream event normalization** — Every driver must produce `StreamEvent` objects. The TUI, cost tracker, and workflow engine all consume these. A driver that drops events or misparses output breaks everything downstream.\n50\t3. **Output contract integrity** — Cross-framework task execution depends on output contracts being complete, correctly serialized, and crash-safe. A corrupted contract means the next task gets garbage context.\n51\t4. **Model resolution cascade** — Task model → agent model → driver default must be consistent across workflow parsing, driver dispatch, and TUI display. A disagreement means the TUI shows one model while the driver uses another.\n52\t\n53\t## Starter Template Evaluation\n54\t\n55\t### Primary Technology Domain\n56\t\n57\tNode.js CLI tool — already built and running. TypeScript + tsup + Commander.js + Vitest. Ink 6 + React 19 for TUI. Published on npm as `codeharness`.\n58\t\n59\t### Starter Options Considered\n60\t\n61\t**N/A — Brownfield project.** The existing technology stack is established:\n62\t\n63\t- TypeScript strict mode, ESM modules\n64\t- tsup for build → `dist/`\n65\t- Commander.js for CLI parsing\n66\t- Vitest + c8 for testing/coverage\n67\t- BATS for bash integration tests\n68\t- Ink 6 + React 19 for terminal UI\n69\t- Claude Code Agent SDK for agent dispatch\n70\t\n71\t### Selected Starter: Existing codebase\n72\t\n73\t**Rationale:** No new project initialization needed. The multi-framework feature adds files to `src/lib/agents/drivers/`, extends `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json`, and adds Ink components to `src/lib/ink-*.tsx`. All within the established architecture.\n74\t\n75\t**New modules to add:**\n76\t\n77\t```\n78\tsrc/lib/agents/drivers/\n79\t├── claude-code.ts      # Refactor existing dispatchAgent() into driver interface\n80\t├── codex.ts            # New — wraps codex CLI\n81\t├── opencode.ts         # New — wraps opencode CLI\n82\t├── factory.ts          # New — driver registry and resolution\n83\t└── types.ts            # Existing — extend AgentDriver interface\n84\t\n85\tsrc/lib/\n86\t├── model-resolver.ts   # New — task → agent → driver default cascade\n87\t├── output-contract.ts  # New — serialize/deserialize cross-framework contracts\n88\t└── ink-workflow.tsx     # New — TUI workflow graph component\n89\t```\n90\t\n91\t**Note:** No project initialization story needed. First story is driver interface formalization.\n92\t\n93\t## Core Architectural Decisions\n94\t\n95\t### Decision 1: Driver Interface Design\n96\t\n97\t**Decision:** Refactor `AgentDriver` interface to support both in-process (Agent SDK) and CLI-wrapped drivers uniformly. `dispatch()` returns `AsyncIterable<StreamEvent>` instead of `spawn()` returning `AgentProcess`.\n98\t\n99\t**Interface:**\n100\t\n101\t```typescript\n102\texport interface AgentDriver {\n103\t  readonly name: string;\n104\t  readonly defaultModel: string;\n105\t  healthCheck(): Promise<DriverHealth>;\n106\t  dispatch(opts: DispatchOpts): AsyncIterable<StreamEvent>;\n107\t  getLastCost(): number | null;\n108\t}\n109\t\n110\tinterface DispatchOpts {\n111\t  prompt: string;\n112\t  model: string;\n113\t  cwd: string;\n114\t  sourceAccess: boolean;\n115\t  plugins?: string[];\n116\t  timeout?: number;\n117\t  outputContract?: OutputContract;\n118\t}\n119\t```\n120\t\n121\t**Rationale:** The workflow engine and TUI consume `StreamEvent` regardless of source. `AsyncIterable` unifies in-process (Agent SDK yields directly) and CLI-wrapped (stdout parsed into events) behind the same consumer interface. Adding new drivers requires implementing `dispatch()` and returning events — no engine changes.\n122\t\n123\t### Decision 2: CLI-Wrapping Strategy\n124\t\n125\t**Decision:** CLI drivers use `child_process.spawn` with stdout line parsing. No PTY allocation. JSON output mode preferred where available.\n126\t\n127\t**Pattern:** Spawn CLI binary with `stdio: ['ignore', 'pipe', 'pipe']`. Parse stdout line-by-line. Each line parsed into `StreamEvent` or null. Yield non-null events from `dispatch()`.\n128\t\n129\t**Health check:** Three-step: (1) `which <binary>` to check installation, (2) version/auth check command, (3) return `{ available, authenticated, version, error? }`.\n130\t\n131\t**Crash detection:** Monitor `proc.exitCode` via Node.js `close` event. Non-zero exit yields `result` event with error classification. Meets NFR13 (<5s detection) — `close` fires immediately.\n132\t\n133\t**Rationale:** No PTY avoids terminal emulation complexity. JSON output mode gives structured data. Line-by-line parsing is simple, streamable, and testable with fixture files.\n134\t\n135\t### Decision 3: Output Contract Format\n136\t\n137\t**Decision:** JSON files in `.codeharness/contracts/{taskName}-{storyId}.json`. Written atomically (write to `.tmp`, rename). Read by next task's prompt injection.\n138\t\n139\t**Contract structure:**\n140\t```json\n141\t{\n142\t  \"version\": 1,\n143\t  \"taskName\": \"implement\",\n144\t  \"storyId\": \"3-1\",\n145\t  \"driver\": \"claude-code\",\n146\t  \"model\": \"claude-opus-4\",\n147\t  \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-03T10:30:00Z\",\n148\t  \"cost_usd\": 0.42,\n149\t  \"duration_ms\": 240000,\n150\t  \"changedFiles\": [\"src/api/users.ts\", \"src/api/users.test.ts\"],\n151\t  \"testResults\": { \"passed\": 12, \"failed\": 0, \"coverage\": 98.5 },\n152\t  \"output\": \"Implementation complete...\",\n153\t  \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n154\t    { \"id\": \"AC1\", \"description\": \"User can register\", \"status\": \"implemented\" }\n155\t  ]\n156\t}\n157\t```\n158\t\n159\t**Injection:** Workflow engine reads contract, appends structured summary to next task's prompt as context.\n160\t\n161\t**Rationale:** JSON is universal across drivers. Atomic writes (NFR15) prevent corruption on crash. Version field allows format evolution. Contracts are debuggable — plain files on disk.\n162\t\n163\t### Decision 4: Model Resolution\n164\t\n165\t**Decision:** Three-level cascade resolved at dispatch time by `model-resolver.ts`.\n166\t\n167\t**Resolution order:**\n168\t1. Task-level `model` in workflow YAML (highest priority)\n169\t2. Agent-level `model` in agent YAML\n170\t3. Driver default model (hard-coded per driver)\n171\t\n172\t**Driver defaults:**\n173\t- `claude-code`: `claude-sonnet-4-20250514`\n174\t- `codex`: `codex-mini`\n175\t- `opencode`: inherits from OpenCode's own config\n176\t\n177\t**Implementation:** `resolveModel(task, agent, driver) → task.model ?? agent.model ?? driver.defaultModel`\n178\t\n179\t**Rationale:** Simple, deterministic, debuggable. Resolved model is logged and displayed in TUI. No magic, no indirection.\n180\t\n181\t### Decision 5: TUI Workflow Graph Component\n182\t\n183\t**Decision:** New `WorkflowGraph` Ink component inserted between Header and StoryBreakdown. Renders a single-line flow with status indicators, driver labels, and cost/time per node.\n184\t\n185\t**Rendering format:**\n186\t```\n187\t━━━ Workflow: story 3-1 ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n188\t  implement ✓  →  verify ◆  →  loop(1)[ retry → verify ]\n189\t  claude-code     codex\n190\t  $0.42 / 4m      ... / 2m\n191\t━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n192\t```\n193\t\n194\t**Status indicators:** pending (dim), active (cyan + spinner), done (green ✓), failed (red ✗). Loop blocks show iteration count.\n195\t\n196\t**Rationale:** Fits existing Ink component pattern. Single-line flow is readable for workflows up to ~5 tasks. Driver and cost info below each node gives full visibility at a glance.\n197\t\n198\t### Decision 6: Plugin Ecosystem Pass-Through\n199\t\n200\t**Decision:** Workflow YAML tasks specify a `plugins` array. Drivers translate to framework-specific CLI flags.\n201\t\n202\t**YAML:** `plugins: ['gstack']` on a claude-code task. `plugins: ['omo']` on an opencode task.\n203\t\n204\t**Driver translation:**\n205\t- `claude-code`: `plugins` → Agent SDK plugin options or `--plugin` flag\n206\t- `opencode`: `plugins` → `--plugin` flag\n207\t- `codex`: plugins not supported → warn and ignore\n208\t\n209\t**Rationale:** Declarative config in YAML. Drivers handle translation. No framework-specific knowledge leaks into the workflow engine.\n210\t\n211\t## Implementation Patterns & Consistency Rules\n212\t\n213\t### Critical Conflict Points\n214\t\n215\t5 areas where AI agents implementing different drivers could diverge:\n216\t\n217\t1. Driver file structure and exports\n218\t2. StreamEvent production from different CLI outputs\n219\t3. Error classification from framework-specific errors\n220\t4. Output contract population from different agent outputs\n221\t5. Health check implementation per driver\n222\t\n223\t### Driver Implementation Pattern\n224\t\n225\t**Every driver MUST follow this structure:**\n226\t\n227\t```typescript\n228\t// src/lib/agents/drivers/{name}.ts\n229\timport type { AgentDriver, DispatchOpts, StreamEvent, DriverHealth } from './types.js';\n230\t\n231\texport class CodexDriver implements AgentDriver {\n232\t  readonly name = 'codex';\n233\t  readonly defaultModel = 'codex-mini';\n234\t  private lastCost: number | null = null;\n235\t\n236\t  async healthCheck(): Promise<DriverHealth> { /* ... */ }\n237\t  async *dispatch(opts: DispatchOpts): AsyncIterable<StreamEvent> { /* ... */ }\n238\t  getLastCost(): number | null { return this.lastCost; }\n239\t}\n240\t```\n241\t\n242\t**Rules:**\n243\t- One file per driver, named `{driver-name}.ts`\n244\t- Class name: `{DriverName}Driver` (PascalCase)\n245\t- Export the class as named export\n246\t- Register in `factory.ts` — never auto-discover\n247\t- Driver MUST be stateless between dispatches (except `lastCost`)\n248\t\n249\t### StreamEvent Production Pattern\n250\t\n251\t**All drivers MUST produce events in this order for a successful dispatch:**\n252\t\n253\t1. Zero or more `tool-start` → `tool-input` → `tool-complete` sequences\n254\t2. Zero or more `text` events (interleaved with tool sequences)\n255\t3. Zero or more `retry` events (if API retries occur)\n256\t4. Exactly one `result` event at the end (with cost_usd and sessionId)\n257\t\n258\t**If the driver cannot map a CLI output line to a StreamEvent, it MUST:**\n259\t- Log the unparseable line at debug level\n260\t- Skip it (yield nothing)\n261\t- Never yield a malformed event\n262\t- Never throw — unparseable lines are expected during format discovery\n263\t\n264\t**Cost reporting:**\n265\t- If the CLI reports cost → set `result.cost_usd`\n266\t- If the CLI does not report cost → set `result.cost_usd = null` (not 0, not undefined)\n267\t\n268\t### Error Classification Pattern\n269\t\n270\t**All drivers MUST classify errors into exactly these categories:**\n271\t\n272\t```typescript\n273\ttype ErrorCategory = 'RATE_LIMIT' | 'NETWORK' | 'AUTH' | 'TIMEOUT' | 'UNKNOWN';\n274\t```\n275\t\n276\t**Classification rules (in priority order):**\n277\t1. HTTP 429 or \"rate limit\" in message → `RATE_LIMIT`\n278\t2. ECONNREFUSED, ETIMEDOUT, ENOTFOUND → `NETWORK`\n279\t3. HTTP 401/403 or \"unauthorized\"/\"forbidden\" → `AUTH`\n280\t4. Process killed by timeout → `TIMEOUT`\n281\t5. Everything else → `UNKNOWN`\n282\t\n283\t**Driver MUST NOT invent new categories.**\n284\t\n285\t### Output Contract Population Pattern\n286\t\n287\t**After each task dispatch, the workflow engine populates an output contract. Drivers MUST:**\n288\t\n289\t- Set `changedFiles` from file modification events (tool-complete for Write/Edit tools)\n290\t- Set `testResults` from parsed test output (if detectable) or `null`\n291\t- Set `output` as the agent's final text response\n292\t- Set `cost_usd` from `getLastCost()`\n293\t- Never fabricate data — if information isn't available, set `null`\n294\t\n295\t### Health Check Pattern\n296\t\n297\t**All drivers MUST implement:**\n298\t\n299\t```typescript\n300\tinterface DriverHealth {\n301\t  available: boolean;     // CLI binary found on PATH\n302\t  authenticated: boolean; // Auth check passed (or N/A)\n303\t  version: string | null; // CLI version string\n304\t  error?: string;         // Human-readable error if !available || !authenticated\n305\t}\n306\t```\n307\t\n308\t**Check sequence:** (1) `which {binary}`, (2) `{binary} --version`, (3) framework-specific auth check.\n309\t\n310\t**If binary not found:** Return with `error` containing install instructions.\n311\t\n312\t### Testing Pattern for Drivers\n313\t\n314\t**Every driver MUST have:**\n315\t- Unit tests with real CLI output fixtures in `test/fixtures/drivers/{name}/`\n316\t- Test that `dispatch()` produces correct `StreamEvent` sequence from fixture\n317\t- Test that `healthCheck()` handles binary-not-found gracefully\n318\t- Test that error classification works for framework-specific errors\n319\t\n320\t**Anti-pattern:** Never mock `child_process.spawn`. Mock at the line-reader level — feed fixture lines to `parseLine()`.\n321\t\n322\t### Enforcement Guidelines\n323\t\n324\t**Code review checklist for new drivers:**\n325\t1. Class implements `AgentDriver` interface? ✓\n326\t2. Registered in `factory.ts`? ✓\n327\t3. `dispatch()` yields events in correct order? ✓\n328\t4. `result` event always emitted (even on error)? ✓\n329\t5. Error classification uses standard categories? ✓\n330\t6. Fixture-based tests exist? ✓\n331\t\n332\t## Project Structure & Boundaries\n333\t\n334\t### New Files (Multi-Framework Extension)\n335\t\n336\t```\n337\tsrc/lib/agents/\n338\t├── drivers/\n339\t│   ├── types.ts              # Extended AgentDriver interface, DispatchOpts, DriverHealth\n340\t│   ├── factory.ts            # NEW — driver registry, getDriver(name), listDrivers()\n341\t│   ├── claude-code.ts        # REFACTOR — extract from agent-dispatch.ts into driver class\n342\t│   ├── codex.ts              # NEW — Codex CLI wrapper driver\n343\t│   └── opencode.ts           # NEW — OpenCode CLI wrapper driver\n344\t├── model-resolver.ts         # NEW — task → agent → driver default cascade\n345\t├── output-contract.ts        # NEW — serialize/deserialize, atomic write, prompt injection\n346\t└── stream-parser.ts          # EXISTING — shared line parsing utilities\n347\t\n348\tsrc/lib/\n349\t├── workflow-parser.ts        # MODIFY — add driver/model/plugins to task schema validation\n350\t├── workflow-engine.ts        # MODIFY — use driver factory, output contracts between tasks\n351\t├── agent-dispatch.ts         # MODIFY — delegate to driver.dispatch() instead of direct SDK\n352\t├── ink-workflow.tsx           # NEW — WorkflowGraph component\n353\t├── ink-components.tsx         # MODIFY — add WorkflowGraph to layout, extend SprintInfo\n354\t├── ink-app.tsx                # MODIFY — render WorkflowGraph between Header and StoryBreakdown\n355\t└── ink-renderer.tsx           # MODIFY — add updateWorkflowState() to RendererHandle\n356\t\n357\tsrc/schemas/\n358\t├── workflow.schema.json       # MODIFY — add driver, model, plugins to task definition\n359\t└── output-contract.schema.json # NEW — JSON Schema for output contract format\n360\t\n361\ttest/\n362\t├── unit/\n363\t│   ├── drivers/\n364\t│   │   ├── claude-code.test.ts\n365\t│   │   ├── codex.test.ts\n366\t│   │   ├── opencode.test.ts\n367\t│   │   ├── factory.test.ts\n368\t│   │   └── model-resolver.test.ts\n369\t│   ├── output-contract.test.ts\n370\t│   └── ink-workflow.test.tsx\n371\t└── fixtures/\n372\t    └── drivers/\n373\t        ├── codex/             # Real captured Codex CLI output samples\n374\t        │   ├── success.jsonl\n375\t        │   ├── error-rate-limit.txt\n376\t        │   └── error-auth.txt\n377\t        └── opencode/          # Real captured OpenCode CLI output samples\n378\t            ├── success.txt\n379\t            ├── error-network.txt\n380\t            └── error-auth.txt\n381\t\n382\t.codeharness/\n383\t└── contracts/                 # Runtime — output contract JSON files per task/story\n384\t```\n385\t\n386\t### Architectural Boundaries\n387\t\n388\t**Driver Boundary:**\n389\t- Drivers ONLY know how to spawn their CLI and parse output → `StreamEvent`\n390\t- Drivers do NOT know about workflows, stories, TUI, or other drivers\n391\t- The workflow engine consumes drivers via `AgentDriver` interface only\n392\t\n393\t**Workflow Engine Boundary:**\n394\t- Engine resolves drivers from factory, resolves models, dispatches tasks\n395\t- Engine writes/reads output contracts between tasks\n396\t- Engine does NOT parse CLI output or know driver internals\n397\t\n398\t**TUI Boundary:**\n399\t- TUI consumes `StreamEvent` and workflow state updates\n400\t- TUI does NOT dispatch drivers or write contracts\n401\t- `WorkflowGraph` component receives flow structure and task states as props\n402\t\n403\t**Output Contract Boundary:**\n404\t- Contracts are JSON files on disk — written by engine, read by engine\n405\t- Contracts are framework-agnostic — same schema regardless of source driver\n406\t- Contracts are injected as prompt context, not as structured API calls\n407\t\n408\t### FR to Structure Mapping\n409\t\n410\t| FR Capability Area | Files |\n411\t|-------------------|-------|\n412\t| Driver Management (FR1-FR6) | `drivers/factory.ts`, `drivers/types.ts`, each driver file |\n413\t| Stream Normalization (FR7-FR10) | Each driver's `parseLine()`, `stream-parser.ts` |\n414\t| Workflow Config (FR11-FR15) | `workflow-parser.ts`, `workflow.schema.json` |\n415\t| Cross-Framework Execution (FR16-FR20) | `output-contract.ts`, `workflow-engine.ts` |\n416\t| Plugin Integration (FR21-FR23) | Each driver's `dispatch()` (plugins → CLI flags) |\n417\t| TUI Workflow Graph (FR24-FR30) | `ink-workflow.tsx`, `ink-app.tsx`, `ink-components.tsx` |\n418\t| TUI Activity Extension (FR31-FR33) | `ink-renderer.tsx`, `ink-activity-components.tsx` |\n419\t| Cost Tracking (FR34-FR36) | `ink-renderer.tsx`, `ink-workflow.tsx` |\n420\t| Driver Capability Matrix (FR37-FR38) | `drivers/factory.ts` (capabilities metadata per driver) |\n421\t\n422\t### Data Flow\n423\t\n424\t```\n425\tWorkflow YAML → workflow-parser → resolved tasks with driver/model\n426\t    ↓\n427\tworkflow-engine → model-resolver → resolved model per task\n428\t    ↓\n429\tdriver-factory → get driver by name → driver.healthCheck()\n430\t    ↓\n431\tdriver.dispatch(opts) → AsyncIterable<StreamEvent>\n432\t    ↓\n433\t    ├→ ink-renderer.update(event) → TUI renders\n434\t    ├→ workflow-engine collects events → output-contract.write()\n435\t    └→ next task: output-contract.read() → inject into prompt\n436\t```\n437\t\n438\t## Architecture Validation Results\n439\t\n440\t### Coherence Validation ✓\n441\t\n442\t**Decision Compatibility:** All 6 decisions are internally consistent. `AsyncIterable<StreamEvent>` from Decision 1 feeds both workflow engine (Decision 3) and TUI (Decision 5). Model resolution (Decision 4) feeds `DispatchOpts.model` from Decision 1. Plugin pass-through (Decision 6) extends `DispatchOpts.plugins`. No contradictions.\n443\t\n444\t**Pattern Consistency:** All drivers follow identical class structure, registration, event ordering, and error classification. Output contracts are framework-agnostic by design.\n445\t\n446\t**Structure Alignment:** Project structure maps cleanly to decisions — `drivers/` for Decisions 1-2, `output-contract.ts` for Decision 3, `model-resolver.ts` for Decision 4, `ink-workflow.tsx` for Decision 5.\n447\t\n448\t### Requirements Coverage ✓\n449\t\n450\t**Functional Requirements:** 38/38 FRs architecturally supported. Every FR capability area maps to specific architectural decisions and source files.\n451\t\n452\t**Non-Functional Requirements:** 18/18 NFRs architecturally supported. Performance NFRs met by design choices (no PTY, Ink 15 FPS, atomic writes). Reliability NFRs met by Node.js close events, debug logging, and contract versioning.\n453\t\n454\t### Gap Analysis\n455\t\n456\t**Critical Gaps:** 0\n457\t\n458\t**Important Gaps (resolved):**\n459\t1. Added `capabilities: DriverCapabilities` to `AgentDriver` interface for FR37-FR38\n460\t2. Added `suggestCheaperDriver()` to `factory.ts` for FR36 cost routing hints\n461\t\n462\t### Architecture Completeness Checklist\n463\t\n464\t- [x] Project context analyzed (brownfield, 38 FRs, 18 NFRs)\n465\t- [x] 6 architectural decisions documented with rationale\n466\t- [x] Implementation patterns defined (driver structure, events, errors, contracts, health, testing)\n467\t- [x] Project structure mapped with FR traceability\n468\t- [x] Architectural boundaries defined (driver, engine, TUI, contract)\n469\t- [x] Data flow documented\n470\t- [x] All FRs and NFRs architecturally supported\n471\t\n472\t### Architecture Readiness Assessment\n473\t\n474\t**Overall Status:** READY FOR IMPLEMENTATION\n475\t**Confidence Level:** High\n476\t\n477\t**First Implementation Priority:** Formalize `AgentDriver` interface and refactor existing Agent SDK dispatch into `ClaudeCodeDriver` class.\n478\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0163BvoEdufpS4RkXNcR2GmH","session_id":"90f775a4-0bf0-4884-b410-4d7f1f50684d","uuid":"06885a17-c0a5-44f4-a003-c65e0c11394c","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:08:39.974Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0195NzNnwDR3e3TVJMrjGgby","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 10.5: Workflow Engine Driver Integration\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want the workflow engine to dispatch tasks through the driver factory instead of calling `dispatchAgent()` directly,\n11\tso that switching drivers is a configuration change, not a code change, and all future drivers work without modifying the engine.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** the existing `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts`\n16\t   **When** the `dispatchTaskWithResult()` function dispatches a task\n17\t   **Then** it resolves the driver via `getDriver()` from the factory (defaulting to `'claude-code'`)\n18\t   **And** calls `driver.dispatch(opts)` instead of calling `dispatchAgent()` directly\n19\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t2. **Given** a `ResolvedTask` without a `driver` field (existing workflows)\n22\t   **When** the engine dispatches the task\n23\t   **Then** it defaults to `getDriver('claude-code')`\n24\t   **And** the workflow executes identically to the pre-refactor behavior\n25\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n26\t\n27\t3. **Given** the engine calls `driver.dispatch(opts)`\n28\t   **When** the dispatch returns `AsyncIterable<StreamEvent>`\n29\t   **Then** the engine consumes all `StreamEvent` objects from the iterable\n30\t   **And** captures the `result` event to extract `output`, `sessionId`, and `cost`\n31\t   **And** builds a `DispatchResult`-compatible object from the stream events\n32\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n33\t\n34\t4. **Given** the engine dispatches a task through the driver\n35\t   **When** the model needs to be resolved\n36\t   **Then** it calls `resolveModel(task, agent, driver)` from `model-resolver.ts`\n37\t   **And** passes the resolved model string in `DispatchOpts.model`\n38\t   **Where** `task` is the `ResolvedTask` (which currently has no `model` field — resolves to agent/driver default)\n39\t   **And** `agent` is an object derived from the `SubagentDefinition` (has `model` field)\n40\t   **And** `driver` is the resolved `AgentDriver` instance (has `defaultModel`)\n41\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n42\t\n43\t5. **Given** a driver's `dispatch()` yields a `result` event with an `error` field\n44\t   **When** the engine processes the stream\n45\t   **Then** it maps the error to a `DispatchError` using the `errorCategory` from the result event\n46\t   **And** existing error handling (halt on RATE_LIMIT/NETWORK/SDK_INIT, continue on UNKNOWN) remains unchanged\n47\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n48\t\n49\t6. **Given** a task with `timeout` configured (or the default timeout)\n50\t   **When** the engine builds `DispatchOpts`\n51\t   **Then** it passes the timeout value through to `DispatchOpts.timeout`\n52\t   **And** the driver is responsible for implementing the timeout (the engine does not set its own timer)\n53\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n54\t\n55\t7. **Given** the engine's `dispatchTaskWithResult()` function\n56\t   **When** it builds the `DispatchOpts` for the driver\n57\t   **Then** the opts include: `prompt`, `model` (from resolveModel), `cwd` (projectDir or isolated workspace), `sourceAccess` (from `task.source_access`)\n58\t   **And** `plugins` is set from `task.plugins` if present (forward-compat, currently undefined on ResolvedTask)\n59\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n60\t\n61\t8. **Given** the old `dispatchAgent()` import in `workflow-engine.ts`\n62\t   **When** the refactor is complete\n63\t   **Then** `dispatchAgent` is no longer imported or called from `workflow-engine.ts`\n64\t   **And** the imports instead include `getDriver` from `./agents/drivers/factory.js` and `resolveModel` from `./agents/model-resolver.js`\n65\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n66\t\n67\t9. **Given** the loop block execution in `executeLoopBlock()`\n68\t   **When** loop tasks dispatch through the driver\n69\t   **Then** the driver integration works identically for loop-block tasks and sequential tasks\n70\t   **And** retry prompts (from evaluator findings) are passed through `DispatchOpts.prompt`\n71\t   **And** verdict parsing from per-run tasks still works (output captured from result event)\n72\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n73\t\n74\t10. **Given** `npm run build` is executed\n75\t    **When** the build completes\n76\t    **Then** it succeeds with zero TypeScript errors\n77\t    **And** `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions in existing test suites\n78\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n79\t\n80\t11. **Given** unit tests in `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts`\n81\t    **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n82\t    **Then** tests verify the engine calls `getDriver()` with the correct driver name\n83\t    **And** tests verify the engine calls `driver.dispatch()` with properly constructed `DispatchOpts`\n84\t    **And** tests verify `resolveModel()` is called with `(task, agent, driver)` arguments\n85\t    **And** tests verify the engine consumes `AsyncIterable<StreamEvent>` and extracts result data\n86\t    **And** tests verify backward compatibility: tasks without `driver` field use `'claude-code'`\n87\t    **And** tests verify error events from the driver stream are mapped to `DispatchError`\n88\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n89\t\n90\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n91\t\n92\t- [x] Task 1: Refactor `dispatchTaskWithResult()` to use driver factory (AC: #1, #2, #3, #7, #8)\n93\t  - [x] Remove `import { dispatchAgent, DispatchError } from './agent-dispatch.js'`\n94\t  - [x] Add `import { getDriver } from './agents/drivers/factory.js'`\n95\t  - [x] Add `import { resolveModel } from './agents/model-resolver.js'`\n96\t  - [x] Resolve driver name from `task.driver ?? 'claude-code'` (forward-compat for when ResolvedTask gets a `driver` field)\n97\t  - [x] Call `getDriver(driverName)` to get the driver instance\n98\t  - [x] Build `DispatchOpts` with: prompt, model (from resolveModel), cwd, sourceAccess, plugins, timeout\n99\t  - [x] Call `driver.dispatch(opts)` and consume the `AsyncIterable<StreamEvent>`\n100\t  - [x] Extract output text, sessionId, and cost from the `result` event\n101\t  - [x] Return a `DispatchResult`-compatible object constructed from stream data\n102\t\n103\t- [x] Task 2: Integrate `resolveModel()` into dispatch flow (AC: #4)\n104\t  - [x] Call `resolveModel(task, agentAsModelSource, driver)` before dispatch\n105\t  - [x] Build `agentAsModelSource` from `SubagentDefinition.model` (map to `{ model: definition.model }`)\n106\t  - [x] Pass resolved model in `DispatchOpts.model`\n107\t\n108\t- [x] Task 3: Map driver error events to DispatchError (AC: #5)\n109\t  - [x] When the result event has an `error` field, throw a `DispatchError`\n110\t  - [x] Map `errorCategory` from the result event to `DispatchErrorCode` (RATE_LIMIT, NETWORK map directly; AUTH/TIMEOUT map to UNKNOWN for now since DispatchErrorCode doesn't have them; or add them)\n111\t  - [x] Preserve existing halt-on-critical-error logic\n112\t\n113\t- [x] Task 4: Handle timeout pass-through (AC: #6)\n114\t  - [x] Pass `task.max_budget_usd` or timeout config through `DispatchOpts.timeout` if available\n115\t  - [x] Remove any engine-level timeout handling for driver calls (driver owns timeout now)\n116\t\n117\t- [x] Task 5: Verify loop block integration (AC: #9)\n118\t  - [x] Confirm `executeLoopBlock()` uses the same dispatch path (it calls `dispatchTask()` / `dispatchTaskWithResult()`)\n119\t  - [x] Verify retry prompts pass through correctly\n120\t  - [x] Verify verdict parsing still works from captured output\n121\t\n122\t- [x] Task 6: Write unit tests (AC: #10, #11)\n123\t  - [x] Mock `getDriver()` to return a fake `AgentDriver` with a controlled `dispatch()` async generator\n124\t  - [x] Mock `resolveModel()` to return a known model string\n125\t  - [x] Test: engine calls `getDriver('claude-code')` when task has no driver field\n126\t  - [x] Test: engine calls `driver.dispatch()` with correct `DispatchOpts` shape\n127\t  - [x] Test: engine extracts output, sessionId, cost from result event\n128\t  - [x] Test: engine maps error result events to `DispatchError`\n129\t  - [x] Test: `resolveModel()` is called with correct arguments\n130\t  - [x] Test: existing sequential + loop block tests still pass\n131\t  - [x] Verify `npm run build` succeeds\n132\t  - [x] Verify `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions\n133\t\n134\t## Dev Notes\n135\t\n136\t### Architecture Compliance\n137\t\n138\tThis story implements the \"Workflow Engine Driver Integration\" from Epic 1 (Story 1.5) in `epics-multi-framework.md`. It is the keystone story that connects the driver abstraction (stories 10-1 through 10-4) to the existing workflow engine.\n139\t\n140\tKey architecture decisions honored:\n141\t- **Decision 1 (Driver Interface):** Engine consumes `AsyncIterable<StreamEvent>` from `driver.dispatch()` — framework-agnostic\n142\t- **Decision 4 (Model Resolution):** Engine calls `resolveModel(task, agent, driver)` before every dispatch\n143\t- **Factory pattern:** Engine uses `getDriver(name)` — no direct driver instantiation\n144\t\n145\t### Current State of the Codebase\n146\t\n147\t- **`workflow-engine.ts`** currently imports and calls `dispatchAgent()` from `agent-dispatch.ts`. This is the old dispatch path — a direct Agent SDK call that returns `DispatchResult` (sessionId, success, durationMs, output).\n148\t- **`dispatchTaskWithResult()`** is the single internal function that all dispatch paths go through (both `dispatchTask()` and loop block execution). Refactoring this one function is sufficient.\n149\t- **`agent-dispatch.ts`** will NOT be deleted — it may still be used by other code paths (e.g., direct CLI invocation outside the workflow engine). But `workflow-engine.ts` should no longer import it.\n150\t- **`DispatchError`** is defined in `agent-dispatch.ts`. The engine currently catches `DispatchError` instances to decide halt vs continue. The refactored engine must still throw/catch `DispatchError` — either by continuing to import the class from `agent-dispatch.ts` (acceptable) or by re-creating the error from driver stream events.\n151\t- **`ResolvedTask`** does NOT currently have a `driver` field or a `model` field. Those come in story 11-1 (Workflow Schema Extension). The engine must use `(task as { driver?: string }).driver ?? 'claude-code'` or similar forward-compatible access.\n152\t- **`SubagentDefinition`** has a `model` field (currently hardcoded to `'claude-sonnet-4-20250514'`). This is used as the agent-level input to `resolveModel()`.\n153\t\n154\t### Stream Consumption Pattern\n155\t\n156\tThe driver's `dispatch()` returns `AsyncIterable<StreamEvent>`. The engine must consume it to completion, collecting:\n157\t\n158\t```typescript\n159\tlet output = '';\n160\tlet sessionId = '';\n161\tlet cost = 0;\n162\t\n163\tfor await (const event of driver.dispatch(opts)) {\n164\t  if (event.type === 'text') {\n165\t    output += event.text;\n166\t  }\n167\t  if (event.type === 'result') {\n168\t    sessionId = event.sessionId;\n169\t    cost = event.cost;\n170\t    if (event.error) {\n171\t      // Map to DispatchError and throw\n172\t    }\n173\t  }\n174\t}\n175\t```\n176\t\n177\tThis replaces the old `dispatchAgent()` call which returned `DispatchResult` directly.\n178\t\n179\t### DispatchError Handling Strategy\n180\t\n181\tTwo options for DispatchError:\n182\t1. **Keep importing `DispatchError` from `agent-dispatch.ts`** — the class is framework-agnostic and only carries a code, message, agentName, and cause. No reason to duplicate it.\n183\t2. **Move `DispatchError` to a shared types file** — cleaner long-term but out of scope for this story.\n184\t\n185\tRecommended: option 1 (keep importing from agent-dispatch). The `DispatchError` import stays; only `dispatchAgent` import is removed.\n186\t\n187\t### What NOT to Do\n188\t\n189\t- Do NOT modify `agent-dispatch.ts` — it remains as-is for backward compat\n190\t- Do NOT add `driver` or `model` fields to `ResolvedTask` — that's story 11-1\n191\t- Do NOT modify `ClaudeCodeDriver` or `factory.ts` — they are done\n192\t- Do NOT modify `model-resolver.ts` — it is done\n193\t- Do NOT modify `workflow-parser.ts` or `workflow.schema.json` — schema extension is story 11-1\n194\t- Do NOT delete `agent-dispatch.ts` — other code paths may still use it\n195\t- Do NOT add driver registration to `workflow-engine.ts` — drivers are registered at application startup (likely in the CLI entry point)\n196\t\n197\t### Driver Registration Prerequisite\n198\t\n199\tThe driver factory must have drivers registered before the engine runs. This likely happens in the CLI entry point (e.g., `src/commands/run.ts` or similar). If no registration exists yet, the engine tests must mock `getDriver()` or call `registerDriver()` in test setup. The engine itself does NOT register drivers.\n200\t\n201\t### Testing Patterns\n202\t\n203\t- Follow existing Vitest patterns in `src/lib/__tests__/`\n204\t- Mock `getDriver` from `./agents/drivers/factory.js` using `vi.mock()`\n205\t- Create a mock `AgentDriver` that returns a controlled async generator from `dispatch()`\n206\t- Mock `resolveModel` to return a fixed string\n207\t- Existing workflow-engine tests (if any) should continue to pass — update their mocks to work with the new dispatch path\n208\t- Use `vi.spyOn` to verify `getDriver` and `resolveModel` are called with expected arguments\n209\t\n210\t### References\n211\t\n212\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md#Decision 1: Driver Interface Design]\n213\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md#Decision 4: Model Resolution]\n214\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md#Story 1.5: Workflow Engine Driver Integration]\n215\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-engine.ts — dispatchTaskWithResult() function]\n216\t- [Source: src/lib/agent-dispatch.ts — dispatchAgent(), DispatchError]\n217\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/drivers/factory.ts — getDriver()]\n218\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/model-resolver.ts — resolveModel()]\n219\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/types.ts — AgentDriver, DispatchOpts]\n220\t\n221\t## Dev Agent Record\n222\t\n223\t### Implementation Plan\n224\t\n225\tRefactored `dispatchTaskWithResult()` in `workflow-engine.ts` to:\n226\t1. Resolve driver via `getDriver(task.driver ?? 'claude-code')` from the factory\n227\t2. Resolve model via `resolveModel(task, {model: definition.model}, driver)` cascade\n228\t3. Build `DispatchOpts` with prompt, model, cwd, sourceAccess, plugins, timeout\n229\t4. Call `driver.dispatch(opts)` and consume `AsyncIterable<StreamEvent>`\n230\t5. Extract output (text events), sessionId, and cost from result event\n231\t6. Map error result events to `DispatchError` with appropriate code mapping\n232\t7. Keep `DispatchError` import from `agent-dispatch.ts` (class is framework-agnostic)\n233\t8. Remove `dispatchAgent` import entirely\n234\t\n235\t### Completion Notes\n236\t\n237\t- Refactored `dispatchTaskWithResult()` — the single dispatch path used by both sequential and loop block execution\n238\t- All 95 existing tests updated to use driver mock instead of `mockDispatchAgent`\n239\t- Added 13 new driver-integration-specific tests covering all ACs\n240\t- Total: 108 tests in workflow-engine.test.ts, all passing\n241\t- Full test suite: 4321 tests across 164 files, zero regressions\n242\t- Build: zero TypeScript errors\n243\t- `DispatchError` still imported from `agent-dispatch.ts` (option 1 from Dev Notes)\n244\t- `dispatchAgent` no longer imported or called from `workflow-engine.ts`\n245\t- ErrorCategory mapping: RATE_LIMIT/NETWORK map directly; AUTH/TIMEOUT map to UNKNOWN\n246\t- `task.max_budget_usd` passed through as `DispatchOpts.timeout`\n247\t- Forward-compat: `(task as { driver?: string }).driver` and `(task as { plugins?: readonly string[] }).plugins`\n248\t\n249\t## File List\n250\t\n251\t- src/lib/workflow-engine.ts (modified) — refactored dispatchTaskWithResult to use driver factory\n252\t- src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts (modified) — updated all mocks + 17 new driver integration tests\n253\t- src/lib/agents/types.ts (modified) — added sessionId and appendSystemPrompt to DispatchOpts\n254\t- src/lib/agents/drivers/claude-code.ts (modified) — thread sessionId and appendSystemPrompt to SDK query\n255\t\n256\t## Change Log\n257\t\n258\t- 2026-04-03: Story 10-5 implemented — workflow engine now dispatches through driver factory instead of calling dispatchAgent() directly. All existing tests adapted, 13 new tests added.\n259\t- 2026-04-03: Code review fixes — restored sessionId and appendSystemPrompt pass-through to DispatchOpts (were silently dropped in refactor), added SDK_INIT to errorCategory mapping, added DispatchOpts fields to types.ts, threaded them through ClaudeCodeDriver. 4 new tests added.\n260\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0163BvoEdufpS4RkXNcR2GmH","session_id":"90f775a4-0bf0-4884-b410-4d7f1f50684d","uuid":"e0330f30-e3f9-417b-99f0-d515be715cb3","timestamp":"2026-04-03T08:08:40.319Z"}
